            ('Explain the difference between copyright and public domain.', ['Copyright: creator\'s exclusive legal right; cannot use without permission (with exceptions like fair use)', 'Public domain: no copyright restrictions; anyone can use, share, or modify freely', 'Works enter public domain after copyright expires (70+ years after creator\'s death in US)', 'US government works are automatically public domain']),
            ('A hiring algorithm was trained on 10 years of hiring data from a male-dominated company. What bias might it learn?', ['Training data: mostly males were hired → algorithm learns to prefer male applicants', 'May penalize resumes with signals of female identity (e.g., women\'s college, certain clubs)', 'Produces discriminatory hiring recommendations despite no explicit gender rule', 'Example: Amazon scrapped such a hiring AI in 2018']),
            ('What is the digital divide and why does it matter?', ['Gap between those with and without access to computing technology and internet', 'Affects education: students without home internet fall behind', 'Affects economic opportunity: remote work and online services require connectivity', 'Matters for equity: technology benefits accrue more to those already advantaged']),
            ('Name two GDPR rights individuals have over their personal data.', ['Right to access: can request what data a company holds on you', 'Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten"): can request deletion', 'Also: right to data portability, right to explanation of automated decisions', 'GDPR applies to any company processing EU residents\' data']),
            ('Why should accessibility be built into software from the start rather than added later?', ['Retrofit is harder and more expensive than designing for accessibility initially', 'Accessibility features (captions, keyboard nav) often improve usability for all', '"Curb cut effect": features for disabled users benefit many others', 'Legal requirements (ADA in US) also apply to software']),
            ('What is machine learning and how is it different from traditional programming?', ['Traditional: programmer writes explicit rules for every case', 'Machine learning: system learns patterns from data automatically', 'No explicit rules coded — model adjusts from examples', 'Enables tasks too complex to hand-code: image recognition, language translation']),
            ('Evaluate: "Encryption helps criminals and should have government backdoors."', ['True: encryption can protect criminal communications', 'Counter: backdoors create vulnerabilities that criminals and foreign governments can also exploit', 'Security experts: backdoors fundamentally weaken encryption for everyone', 'Strong encryption protects citizens, businesses, and critical infrastructure']),
